                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14277557" author="enis" created="Wed, 14 Jan 2015 19:48:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IntegrationTestsDriver is good for running a set of tests, or all tests with the default configuration. However, what we have found out here is that we need to custom configure some of the tests (like before this test, enable this configuration or run this test with these parameters once, and run it again with these parameters). IntegrationTestsDriver does not allow this easily. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus I would prefer the tests to be runnable on their own with main methods. But still an easier way to run the tests with default params (through mvn or ITD) is still useful.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14277599" author="eclark" created="Wed, 14 Jan 2015 20:17:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think that I&apos;ve ever run the tests successfully from maven. So for me that&apos;s not really something I value too much. For me I think that the main methods are more important. Also making those main methods all take the same params that are parsed the same way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14278100" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 15 Jan 2015 02:05:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to see all of them have main methods. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14278149" author="dimaspivak" created="Thu, 15 Jan 2015 02:38:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;main() it is! Thanks, gang. I&apos;ll get on this later today or tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14279077" author="ndimiduk" created="Thu, 15 Jan 2015 18:38:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Having 3 different invocation strategies has resulted in bugs, as setup logic tends to be slightly different for mvn vs main vs ITR. I&apos;m in agreement with the quorum.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
